@node "Introduction" "Introduction"


                          @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 Some years ago there appeared a musicformat called @{" Noisepacker 2.0 " link "Noisepacker_2.0" 0}
 and no player was able to deal with it, the program itself couldn`t
 make a Noisetrackermodule out of that stuff it produced and I absolutely
 wanted to play the wonderful module of Phenomena`s enigma demo. What to do ?
 So I decided to write a little tool doing this task to convert
 that module back into a Noisetracker one. Noisedepacker 1.0 was born.

 Some time later my friend Jan started to write the @{"Eagleplayer" link "Eagleplayer" 0}. We
 included lots of Trackerformats and the program got bigger and bigger.
 Then came the idea: Why not converting the modules back to protracker
 and playing them with only one replay to save memory and to make adding
 of features easier ? So I took out my ASM-One and started to write routines
 for doing that task. In this program you`ll find all the routines of Eagle-
 player`s internal Protracker cloned replays.

 I also included some Routines to save the modules in other formats than
 Protracker`s. For example you can save your modules directly as @{"IFF EMOD" link "EMOD_Save" 0}
 if you prefer to use Quadracomposer instead of Protracker.
@endnode

@node "System_requirements" "System requirements"


                       @{b}@{u}System requirements@{ub}@{uu}

 You need Kickstart 2.04 or higher to run Noiseconverter. It uses lots of
 2.x features so you`ll have to upgrade to OS2.x before attempting to start
 this program. It requires the @{"reqtools.library" link "reqtools.library" 0} by Nico Francois,
 available everywhere on the PD market. Except of this you`ll need a little
 bit ram space due to some special features. As you might know today`s mods
 are rather big and Noiseconverter needs at least double the size
 of the module for it`s purposes.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

                         Installation
                         ------------

Just drag Noiseconverter`s icon to the directory of your choice. If you want to use the
locale.library you have to copy the supplied catalog file(s) to "locale:catalogs/".
Furthermore you have to make sure that you installed the reqtools.library in libs,
version 38 or higher. If not, copy the file @{" reqtools.library " link "reqtools.library" 0} to "libs:". To decrunch
files @{" xpkmaster.library " link "XPK" 0} and @{" xfdmaster.library " link "XFDMaster.library" 0} are recommended to use.
@endnode

@node "Starting_" "Starting "


Just double click it from workbench or type it`s name into your cli/shell and press
enter. The Program will attempt to open the @{"reqtools.library" link "reqtools.library" 0} and when it succeeds a
window will appear on your default public Screen (normally Workbench) containing some
gadgets.
@endnode

@node "How_to_use_-->" "How to use -->"

 
 After a successful start you`ll see the main gui with some gadgets
 and listviews in front of you.

 @{" Gadgets Description " link "Gadgets_Description" 0}
 @{" Menus Description   " link "Menus_Description" 0}
 @{" The Ripper Window   " link "The_Ripper_Window" 0}
@endnode

@node "Gadgets_Description" "Gadgets Description"


  You`ll find 3 buttons and 2 listviews and a status gadget in the  gui.  To
  load   a  module  you  just  have  to  select  the  "Load"  button  and  a
  filerequester will appear where you may select the file  of  your  choice.
  After  loading  that  file  Noiseconverter will tell you about what it did
  with your module. When the format of this file is unknown a second  window
  will pop up which is responsible for Noiseconverter`s ripping features.


[Load] (the leftmost button) - opens a filerequester to load the module you 
 (Key "L")                     wanna convert

[Save] (the middle one)      - opens the filerequester to save the current
 (Key "S")                     module. After that the module will be
                               converted into the chosen "Save"-Format (see
                               below) and saved.
                               When no module was loaded or something went
                               wrong an error message will be shown.

[Help] (the right button)    - pops up some requesters for immediate
 (Key "H")                     informations about the program and how to
                               get along. Just click on the gadget of your
                               choice to get to know what to do.

[Status] - informations about the last action, actual state or something
           alike (nothing to click here)

[Informations] - If you loaded a module everything about it will be shown
                 here, name, sizes, length, duration, load format etc. 
                 There are also some special features, from here you access
                 the features to @{"rename the module" link "rename_mod" 0} and @{"rename/save the samples" link "rename_Sam" 0}.

[Save Format]  - In this listview you select the format in which the
                 current module is to be saved. Just click once onto the
                 chosen one and select "Save". The other possibility is to
                 double click on the format of your choice, this has the same
                 effect like selecting the "Save" button.
                 @{"The Save formats and some (insider) background informations" link "SaveFormats" 0}
@endnode

